Ask HN: Why are there fewer low-income families living in U.S. cities nowadays?
text:
I just finished watching a movie that was based in one of Hong Kong's most densely populated districts and it struck me that there really aren't cities like that in the United States. Based on the little history I do know, it seems like New York City used to have a pretty large population of lower income families.

I don't know if there are any good materials to read up on this, I honestly don't even know where to look. I'd just like to learn about what changed policy-wise, culture-wise, economically, etc.

Tell HN: Vertical Tabs in Brave
text:
There's now a feature flag in the Nightly and Dev releases of Brave that enables vertical tabs.[1]

This can be toggled in brave://flags on version 1.45 or later. This requires restarting the browser.

It doesn't currently support nesting (hopefully coming soon?), but you can do tab groups.

I haven't tested long enough to be able to know how stable this is, but I use the Dev build and in general it is fine.

I'm not affiliated with Brave or the dev who built the feature. I'm just a happy Brave user who has been searching for get tabbed browsing for a very long time!

1: https://github.com/brave/brave-core/pull/13816#issuecomment-1262205165
